June 17, 2019 at 1:03 PM ·

Breckenridge High School participates in the myCollegeOptions program which tracks kids' post-secondary education options. According to their data:

33.5% of our kids plan to pursue a Science, Technology, Engineering, or Math (STEM) career versus 26.1% nationally;

38.9% will be the first in their families to attend college; and

91.6% plan to attend a four-year institution.

Breckenridge Chamber of Commerce
January 24, 2019 at 11:17 AM ·

TEXAS STATE TECHNICAL COLLEGE TO HOST LUNCH AND LEARN

Texas State Technical College is hosting a Lunch and Learn at the Breckenridge Campus! Not only will you learn about the technical and safety classes for our diversified manufacturing, aviation, logistics, healthcare, and energy industry partners, you will also hear a presentations from our Career Placement office, Texas Workforce Commission, and companies that have already taken advantage of TSTC's training programs. In addition, you will learn how your company can take advantage of FREE training through the Skills Development Fund and Skills for Small Business grants!

DATE: Thursday, February 28, 2019
TIME: 11:30 am - 1 pm
LOCATION: Breckenridge Campus

Please send your R.S.V.P. to John.Dosher@TSTC.edu

Breckenridge High School
October 24, 2018 at 5:57 PM ·

I have to brag on our Buckaroos for a minute...

In the past week I’ve received two positive reports from people outside of Breckenridge who were visiting our campus. They were very complimentary and said our students were kind and had excellent manners.

I was very proud to hear this, although I wasn’t surprised. It’s great to know we have a community that values citizenship and positive relationships. It speaks well to the future of our community...we’re in great hands moving forward. Great job, Bucks!

Breckenridge North Elementary
March 7, 2018 at 9:34 AM ·

We are excited to announce that this Friday is North Elementary's Where Ya Headed College/Armed Forces Day! Last year we had a huge turnout for career day, and decided to make college and armed forces a focus for this year! We will return to career day next year!
Our students will have the opportunity to talk with several area colleges!
The following is our schedule for speakers:
8:30 Sgt. Olivarez-United States Marine Corps
9:00 McMurry University
10:30 Cisco Collete
1:00 Ranger College
2:00 TSTC Breckenridge
The students will also be working on college related activities throughout the day.
We are so thankful they will be here to talk to our students. Shout outs to Mrs. Deen and Ms. Vicki for setting up our speakers, and to Mrs. Deen, Mrs. Gillard, and PTO Representative Meredith Wunsch for contacting universities all over Texas for information and giveaway items!
We hope ALL of our North students will be here on Friday for this speacial event!

Canyon Road Barn & Grill
December 5, 2017 at 12:18 PM ·

Starting next Tuesday, December 5th apply in person beginning at 5pm. Must be 18 years old or older. No prior experience required. We will train the persons with the right attitude and work ethic! Must have reliable Transportation. Must be able to make large deposits in your bank account :) If you are planning on going to college next fall this is ideal training for college town employment! It is not a 9 to 5 M-F job! Your friends and family will be goofing off spending money and you will be making money...welcome to adulting. Predominately Friday, Saturday and peak holiday shifts available. If you have worked here before and realized that you left a really good job, don't waste your time. THIS IS A NEW TALENT CALL! If you have experience and have not worked here before, please come and fill out an app!:) We will be kicking in some fuel expense for those who are willing to drive more than 30-miles! COME FOR THE WORK AND STAY FOR THE CASH!!!

Robert Burchett Jr
October 25, 2017 at 9:47 PM ·

I'm not one to brag about a lesson I taught, but today is an exception. My math classes designed floor plans of their own homes today to set up scale factors tomorrow. I had several kiddos tell me that they never have considered architecture as a career choice, but after doing what we did today, they're going to look in to it. As teachers our job is to inspire, THAT happened in my classroom today.#whereyaheaded #ihaveawesomekiddos

post_text:
Today is the official beginning of the Where Ya Headed campaign. Our focus is for every kid to be able to answer three questions. What do you want to be? What does it take to get there? How is everything I do at school everyday relevant to that?

This requires that teachers and administrators, along with parents and community members, engage in these conversations with our kids, early and often.

You will see more signs, posters, and events, related to this theme. We want to ask kids, ourselves, and our community, "Where ya headed?"
